@SteveS10580971 Ah. If you're worried that the vaccine may make covid more deadly then Australia is not the place to look at as we didn't have enough COVID. There is a good analysis of other countries though on twitter somewhere. I'll try and dig it up

@cookespring It's as good as it can be. Omicron hit Australia december 2021 and so it stops being a good place to look for any vaccine-induced deaths at that point. But the entire country was >80% double vaxxed by then-with no sign of any vaccine-induced increase in mortality

@SteveS10580971 I agree. Australia is not over COVID. The point of the thread is that Australia is one of the few countries where COVID deaths have not complicated the all-cause mortality numbers. So its a perfect place to look for any increased deaths due to vaccines. so far there isnt any
